routes.name: Dig it? 1 E2 5b
routes.description: Great climbing. Takes the line up the gently overhanging arete on the left side of the tall part of the crag. Start just to the right of a grassy step. Climb up to reach a right trending crackline. Follow this crack to a footledge, arrange gear, then climb up and left on a series of slopers and crimps (bold) to where the arete kicks back and gear can be placed. Climb this to the top. From here proceed to the base of the gully. Pitch 1. Its best to set up a belay here, as a slip of the first rocky step will send you tumbling till you hit the lake.
